parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or seize, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel seizes
the power steering assist fault message is displayed
the traction control warning light is illuminated
and grinding or popping noises are heard when turning the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the windshield trim can cause a hazard on the road, potentially leading to accidents or injuries to other drivers.
symptoms: The windshield trim panel flies off or detaches while driving
often at high speeds
and may hit other vehicles or cause a distraction to the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the A-pillar trim can cause a hazard on the road, potentially leading to accidents or injuries to other drivers.
symptoms: The A-pillar trim panel flies off or detaches while driving
often at high speeds
and may hit other vehicles or cause a distraction to the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Carbon monoxide leaks can cause serious health risks, including headaches, dizziness, and even death, to occupants of the vehicle.
symptoms: The carbon monoxide detector goes off
and occupants may experience symptoms such as headaches
dizziness
or nausea.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission issues can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or injuries to occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden loss of power
stalling
or unusual noises
and the "switch to park" warning light may appear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power steering failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries to occupants.
symptoms: The power steering assist warning light is illuminated
and the steering wheel may seize or become difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air conditioning issues can cause discomfort and distraction to occupants, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioning is not blowing cold air
and a hissing noise may be present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transfer case failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or injuries to occupants.
symptoms: The transfer case may make unusual noises
such as screeching or clicking
and the vehicle may become undriveable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water pump leaks can cause engine damage and overheating, leading to accidents or injuries to occupants.
symptoms: The water pump may leak coolant
causing the engine to overheat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sunroof leaks can cause water damage and electrical issues, potentially leading to accidents or injuries to occupants.
symptoms: Water may leak through the sunroof
causing damage to the headliner and electrical components
and the master power door switch keypad may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the windshield trim panel can cause a distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents, and can also cause damage to other vehicles or pedestrians if the detached panel strikes them.
symptoms: The windshield trim panel detaches from the vehicle while driving
making a loud noise
and potentially striking other vehicles or pedestrians.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks into the vehicle can cause damage to the electrical systems, carpets, and other components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing safety hazards.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle through the windshield
doors
or trunk
causing water to accumulate on the floorboards
carpets
and other areas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Structural damage to the vehicle can compromise its integrity, leading to accidents or injuries in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Rust or damage to the frame of the vehicle
which can cause structural weakness and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
